---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Syota Sasaki — a freelance software engineer working on GIS, remote sensing, and machine learning. Currently open to new projects."
	pubDate={new Date('Apr 27 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Hi, I'm Syota Sasaki — a freelance software engineer based in Aomori, Japan. I work at the
		intersection of GIS, remote sensing, and machine learning, and this blog is where I write
		about the problems I run into and the things I learn along the way.
	</p>

	<p>
		My path here wasn't a straight line. I studied electronics and hydrology at university and
		earned my degrees in those fields, then spent a few years as a postdoctoral researcher
		before moving from academia into industry. I have been working as a freelance engineer
		since 2022.
	</p>

	<p>
		These days, my projects span geospatial systems, satellite-imagery pipelines, point-cloud
		processing, and the occasional 3D-map web application. The work tends to sit in the gap
		between research-grade technique and production-grade code, which is also what most of the
		writing here will be about. Side projects and engineering essays show up too, whenever
		something feels worth writing down.
	</p>

	<p>
		If any of this resonates and you're working on something in GIS, remote sensing, or ML — or
		just want to talk about it — feel free to reach out. I'm always open to interesting
		projects and conversations.
	</p>
</Layout>
